  "output": "## Test Coverage Analysis — `apps/crawler`\n\n**Baseline: zero test coverage.** `pytest>=9.1.1` is declared as a dev dependency in `pyproject.toml:13`, but no `tests/` directory or `test_*.py` file exists anywhere in the app. Everything below is a gap.\n\nScope: `base.py` (crawl pipeline + parsing helpers), `providers.py` (11 site configs + 3 with custom crawl logic), `models.py` (dataclasses), `main.py` (CLI).\n\n---\n\n### 1. `base.py` — pure helper functions (highest value/effort ratio)\n\n**`parse_french_date` (base.py:90-104)** — untested. Two regex branches, an accent-variant lookup table, several failure modes.\n\n```python\n# tests/test_base.py\nimport pytest\nfrom base import parse_french_date\n\n@pytest.mark.parametrize(\"text,expected\", [\n    (\"22 juin 2019\", \"2019-06-22\"),\n    (\"octobre 30, 2017\", \"2017-10-30\"),\n    (\"1 août 2020\", \"2020-08-01\"),          # accented month\n    (\"1 aout 2020\", \"2020-08-01\"),          # unaccented variant, same month\n    (\"Publié le 5 décembre 2021\", \"2021-12-05\"),  # embedded in surrounding text\n    (\"5 DECEMBRE 2021\", \"2021-12-05\"),      # case-insensitivity\n])\ndef test_parse_french_date_valid(text, expected):\n    assert parse_french_date(text) == expected\n\n@pytest.mark.parametrize(\"text\", [\n    \"\",\n    \"not a date at all\",\n    \"5 blorptember 2021\",   # unrecognized month name\n    \"32 juin 2019\",         # invalid day — currently NOT validated, will raise or silently produce bad ISO\n])\ndef test_parse_french_date_invalid_or_edge(text):\n    # for \"32 juin 2019\": datetime(...) raises ValueError — parse_french_date does not\n    # catch it, so this currently propagates uncaught. That's a gap to confirm/fix.\n    result = parse_french_date(text)\n    assert result is None or isinstance(result, str)\n```\n\nFlag: **no bounds validation** on day/month before constructing `datetime(...)` — a malformed but regex-matching date (`32 juin 2019`, `1 juin 0000`) raises