      {
        "title": "tests/test_base.py",
        "content": "import pytest\nfrom base import parse_french_date\n\n@pytest.mark.parametrize(\"text,expected\", [\n    (\"22 juin 2019\", \"2019-06-22\"),\n    (\"octobre 30, 2017\", \"2017-10-30\"),\n    (\"1 août 2020\", \"2020-08-01\"),          # accented month\n    (\"1 aout 2020\", \"2020-08-01\"),          # unaccented variant, same month\n    (\"Publié le 5 décembre 2021\", \"2021-12-05\"),  # embedded in surrounding text\n    (\"5 DECEMBRE 2021\", \"2021-12-05\"),      # case-insensitivity\n])\ndef test_parse_french_date_valid(text, expected):\n    assert parse_french_date(text) == expected\n\n@pytest.mark.parametrize(\"text\", [\n    \"\",\n    \"not a date at all\",\n    \"5 blorptember 2021\",   # unrecognized month name\n    \"32 juin 2019\",         # invalid day — currently NOT validated, will raise or silently produce bad ISO\n])\ndef test_parse_french_date_invalid_or_edge(text):\n    # for \"32 juin 2019\": datetime(...) raises ValueError — parse_french_date does not\n    # catch it, so this currently propagates uncaught. That's a gap to confirm/fix.\n    result = parse_french_date(text)\n    assert result is None or isinstance(result, str)\n```\n\nFlag: **no bounds validation** on day/month before constructing `datetime(...)` — a malformed but regex-matching date (`32 juin 2019`, `1 juin 0000`) raises `ValueError` uncaught, in both `parse_french_date` and `parse_numeric_date`. Worth a dedicated test asserting current behavior (raises) so a future fix has a red test to go green.\n\n**`parse_numeric_date` (base.py:107-113)** — same gap pattern.\n\n```python\n@pytest.mark.parametrize(\"text,expected\", [\n    (\"22/06/2019\", \"2019-06-22\"),\n    (\"22/06/2019 14:30\", \"2019-06-22\"),   # trailing time ignored\n    (\"no date here\", None),\n])\ndef test_parse_numeric_date(text, expected):\n    assert parse_numeric_date(text) == expected\n\ndef test_parse_numeric_date_invalid_calendar_date_raises():\n    with pytest.raises(ValueError):\n        parse_numeric_date(\"31/02/2019\")  # Feb 31 doesn't exist\n```\n\n**`discover_sitemap_urls` (base.py:61-87)** — untested generator with real branching (sitemapindex recursion, namespace-stripped `loc` matching, image-sitemap nesting exclusion, gzip/leading-newline handling in `_fetch_xml`).\n\n```python\nfrom unittest.mock import patch\nfrom base import discover_sitemap_urls\n\nFLAT_SITEMAP = b\"\"\"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<urlset xmlns=\"http://www.sitemaps.org/schemas/sitemap/0.9\">\n  <url><loc>https://site.mg/a</loc></url>\n  <url><loc>https://site.mg/b</loc>\n    <image:image xmlns:image=\"http://www.google.com/schemas/sitemap-image/1.1\">\n      <image:loc>https://site.mg/img.jpg</image:loc>\n    </image:image>\n  </url>\n</urlset>\"\"\"\n\nINDEX_SITEMAP = b\"\"\"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<sitemapindex xmlns=\"http://www.sitemaps.org/schemas/sitemap/0.9\">\n  <sitemap><loc>https://site.mg/sub1.xml</loc></sitemap>\n</sitemapindex>\"\"\"\n\ndef test_discover_sitemap_urls_flat_excludes_nested_image_loc():\n    with patch(\"base._fetch_xml\", return_value=FLAT_SITEMAP.decode()):\n        urls = list(discover_sitemap_urls(\"https://site.mg/sitemap.xml\"))\n    assert urls == [\"https://site.mg/a\", \"https://site.mg/b\"]  # img.jpg must NOT appear\n\ndef test_discover_sitemap_urls_index_recurses_into_sub_sitemaps():\n    responses = {\"https://site.mg/sitemap.xml\": INDEX_SITEMAP.decode(),\n                 \"https://site.mg/sub1.xml\": FLAT_SITEMAP.decode()}\n    with patch(\"base._fetch_xml\", side_effect=lambda url: responses[url]):\n        urls = list(discover_sitemap_urls(\"https://site.mg/sitemap.xml\"))\n    assert urls == [\"https://site.mg/a\", \"https://site.mg/b\"]\n\ndef test_fetch_xml_handles_gzip_and_leading_newline():\n    import gzip\n    from base import _fetch_xml\n    payload = gzip.compress(b\"\\n<?xml version='1.0'?><a/>\")\n    fake_resp = MagicMock()\n    fake_resp.read.return_value = payload\n    fake_resp.__enter__.return_value = fake_resp\n    with patch(\"urllib.request.urlopen\", return_value=fake_resp):\n        assert _fetch_xml(\"https://x\").startswith(\"<?xml\")\n```\n\n**No test for `_fetch_xml` network failure propagation** (timeout, `URLError`) — currently uncaught inside `_fetch_xml`/`discover_sitemap_urls`; relied upon to bubble to `crawl()`'s outer `except`. Needs an integration-level test (see §3).\n\n---\n\n",
