      {
        "title": "4. `providers.py` — custom per-provider logic",
        "content": "\nMost of the 11 providers are pure declarative `SiteSelectors` configs (low test value beyond a structural smoke test — see §5). Three providers have real logic and zero tests:\n\n**`MadagascarTribune._is_article_link` (providers.py:72-80)** — pure function, ideal for exhaustive parametrization:\n\n```python\nfrom providers import MadagascarTribune\n\n@pytest.mark.parametrize(\"href,expected\", [\n    (\"mon-article.html\", True),\n    (None, False),\n    (\"mon-article\", False),                      # no .html\n    (\"rubrique-.html\", False),                    # category convention excluded\n    (\"https://other.com/a.html\", False),          # absolute/external excluded\n    (\"/mon-article.html\", False),                 # absolute path excluded\n    (\"_Jean-Dupont,1234.html\", False),             # author/keyword page excluded\n])\ndef test_is_article_link(href, expected):\n    assert MadagascarTribune._is_article_link(href) is expected\n```\n\n**`MadagascarTribune._discover_categories` (providers.py:62-70)** — regex-extract + dedupe + sort-by-int; homepage fetch failure → `[]`.\n\n```python\ndef test_discover_categories_dedupes_and_sorts_numerically(monkeypatch):\n    fake_home = MagicMock(html_content='<a href=\"spip.php?rubrique10\">x</a><a href=\"spip.php?rubrique2\">y</a><a href=\"spip.php?rubrique2\">dup</a>')\n    with patch(\"providers.Fetcher.get\", return_value=fake_home):\n        cats = MadagascarTribune()._discover_categories()\n    assert cats == [\n        \"https://madagascar-tribune.com/spip.php?rubrique2\",\n        \"https://madagascar-tribune.com/spip.php?rubrique10\",  # numeric sort, not lexical\n    ]\n\ndef test_discover_categories_returns_empty_on_fetch_failure():\n    with patch(\"providers.Fetcher.get\", side_effect=ConnectionError):\n        assert MadagascarTribune()._discover_categories() == []\n```\n\n**`MadagascarTribune.list_article_urls` (providers.py:82-111)** — pagination loop: stops when a page yields zero new article links, stops on fetch exception, follows the first-fetch redirect (`page.url` reassignment). No test covers the \"0 links on page → break to next category\" boundary, or the redirect-URL propagation into subsequent `?debut_articles=` pagination requests.\n\n**`FreeNews.list_article_urls` (providers.py:173-191)** — API pagination: HTTP 400 → clean stop (end of pages); other `HTTPError` codes → re-raise; empty `posts` list → stop; page increments correctly.\n\n```python\nimport urllib.error\nfrom providers import FreeNews\n\ndef test_freenews_stops_on_400_past_last_page(monkeypatch):\n    def fake_urlopen(req, timeout):\n        raise urllib.error.HTTPError(req.full_url, 400, \"bad\", {}, None)\n    with patch(\"providers.urllib.request.urlopen\", side_effect=fake_urlopen):\n        assert list(FreeNews().list_article_urls()) == []\n\ndef test_freenews_reraises_non_400_http_errors(monkeypatch):\n    def fake_urlopen(req, timeout):\n        raise urllib.error.HTTPError(req.full_url, 500, \"err\", {}, None)\n    with patch(\"providers.urllib.request.urlopen\", side_effect=fake_urlopen):\n        with pytest.raises(urllib.error.HTTPError):\n            list(FreeNews().list_article_urls())\n\ndef test_freenews_paginates_until_empty_page(monkeypatch):\n    pages = {1: [{\"link\": \"https://a\"}], 2: [{\"link\": \"https://b\"}], 3: []}\n    def fake_urlopen(req, timeout):\n        page_num = int(req.full_url.split(\"page=\")[1].split(\"&\")[0]) if \"page=\" in req.full_url else 1\n        resp = MagicMock(); resp.read.return_value = json.dumps(pages.get(page_num, [])).encode()\n        resp.__enter__.return_value = resp\n        return resp\n    with patch(\"providers.urllib.request.urlopen\", side_effect=fake_urlopen):\n        assert list(FreeNews().list_article_urls()) == [\"https://a\", \"https://b\"]\n```\n\n**`Moov.list_article_urls` (providers.py:212-236)** — BFS frontier: dedup via `queued` set, filters non-`/article/` links, continues past a page that fails to fetch during frontier expansion (still yields the URL itself before attempting expansion — note the `yield url` happens *before* the `try/except Fetcher.get`, so a page that 404s is still yielded and handed to `parse_article`, which will then fail there and get logged/retried by `crawl()`. Worth a test asserting this ordering explicitly, since it's easy to accidentally \"fix\" into a regression).\n\n```python\ndef test_moov_bfs_dedupes_and_yields_before_expansion_failure(monkeypatch):\n    home = MagicMock()\n    home.css.return_value = [MagicMock(attrib={\"href\": \"/article/1\"})]\n    page1 = MagicMock()\n    page1.css.return_value = [MagicMock(attrib={\"href\": \"/article/1\"}),  # dup, ignored\n                               MagicMock(attrib={\"href\": \"/other/2\"})]   # not /article/, ignored\n    with patch(\"providers.Fetcher.get\", side_effect=[home, ConnectionError()]):\n        urls = list(Moov().list_article_urls())\n    assert urls == [\"https://new.moov.mg/article/1\"]  # yielded even though its own expansion fetch fails\n```\n\n---\n\n",
        "level": 3
      },
      {
        "title": "5. Missing integration/structural tests",
        "content": "\n**Provider registry sanity (providers.py:279-291)** — nothing currently asserts the registry is internally consistent. Cheap, high-value, catches copy-paste config mistakes immediately:\n\n```python\nfrom providers import PROVIDERS\n\n@pytest.mark.parametrize(\"name,cls\", PROVIDERS.items())\ndef test_provider_dict_key_matches_source_name(name, cls):\n    assert cls.source_name == name\n\n@pytest.mark.parametrize(\"name,cls\", PROVIDERS.items())\ndef test_provider_has_required_selectors(name, cls):\n    assert cls.selectors.title\n    assert cls.selectors.body\n\ndef test_provider_source_names_are_unique():\n    names = [cls.source_name for cls in PROVIDERS.values()]\n    assert len(names) == len(set(names))\n\n@pytest.mark.parametrize(\"name,cls\", PROVIDERS.items())\ndef test_provider_declares_sitemap_or_overrides_list_article_urls(name, cls):\n    has_sitemap = cls.sitemap_url is not None\n    overrides = cls.list_article_urls is not NewsSource.list_article_urls\n    assert has_sitemap or overrides, f\"{name}: no sitemap_url and no custom list_article_urls override\"\n```\n\n**`main.py` — zero coverage.** No test verifies argparse wiring, the `\"all\"` expansion, `--limit` plumbing, or the `on_save` print callback.\n\n```python\n",
        "level": 3
      },
      {
        "title": "tests/test_main.py",
        "content": "import sys\nfrom unittest.mock import patch, MagicMock\nimport main as main_module\n\ndef test_main_crawls_single_provider_with_limit(monkeypatch, capsys):\n    fake_source = MagicMock()\n    fake_source.crawl.return_value = []\n    fake_source._data_path = \"d\"; fake_source._state_path = \"s\"; fake_source._log_path = \"l\"\n    fake_cls = MagicMock(return_value=fake_source)\n    monkeypatch.setattr(main_module, \"PROVIDERS\", {\"newsmada\": fake_cls})\n    monkeypatch.setattr(sys, \"argv\", [\"main.py\", \"newsmada\", \"--limit\", \"5\"])\n    main_module.main()\n    fake_source.crawl.assert_called_once()\n    assert fake_source.crawl.call_args.kwargs[\"limit\"] == 5\n\ndef test_main_all_iterates_every_provider(monkeypatch, capsys):\n    sources = {n: MagicMock(crawl=MagicMock(return_value=[])) for n in (\"a\", \"b\")}\n    for s in sources.values():\n        s._data_path = s._state_path = s._log_path = \"x\"\n    monkeypatch.setattr(main_module, \"PROVIDERS\", {n: MagicMock(return_value=s) for n, s in sources.items()})\n    monkeypatch.setattr(sys, \"argv\", [\"main.py\", \"all\"])\n    main_module.main()\n    for s in sources.values():\n        s.crawl.assert_called_once()\n\ndef test_main_rejects_unknown_provider(monkeypatch):\n    monkeypatch.setattr(sys, \"argv\", [\"main.py\", \"not-a-real-provider\"])\n    with pytest.raises(SystemExit):\n        main_module.main()\n\ndef test_on_save_callback_prints_title_and_date(monkeypatch, capsys):\n    from models import Article\n    fake_source = MagicMock()\n    def fake_crawl(limit, on_save):\n        on_save(Article(url=\"u\", title=\"Hello\", body=\"b\", author=None,\n                         published_date=\"2024-01-01\", category=None, source=\"x\", scraped_at=\"t\"))\n        return []\n    fake_source.crawl.side_effect = fake_crawl\n    fake_source._data_path = fake_source._state_path = fake_source._log_path = \"x\"\n    monkeypatch.setattr(main_module, \"PROVIDERS\", {\"x\": MagicMock(return_value=fake_source)})\n    monkeypatch.setattr(sys, \"argv\", [\"main.py\", \"x\"])\n    main_module.main()\n    assert \"'Hello'\" in capsys.readouterr().out\n```\n\n**`models.py` — one real edge case worth a test:** `Article.images` uses `field(default_factory=list)`, correctly avoiding the classic mutable-default-argument bug. Worth a regression test precisely because it'd be easy for someone to \"simplify\" it to `images: list[str] = []` later and silently reintroduce shared-list state:\n\n```python\nfrom models import Article\n\ndef test_article_images_default_is_not_shared_between_instances():\n    a1 = Article(url=\"u1\", title=\"t\", body=\"b\", author=None, published_date=None,\n                 category=None, source=\"s\", scraped_at=\"ts\")\n    a2 = Article(url=\"u2\", title=\"t\", body=\"b\", author=None, published_date=None,\n                 category=None, source=\"s\", scraped_at=\"ts\")\n    a1.images.append(\"https://x/img.jpg\")\n    assert a2.images == []\n```\n\n---\n\n",
        "level": 1
      },
