        "title": "Summary / priority order",
        "content": "| Priority | Area | Why |\n|---|---|---|\n| 1 | `NewsSource.crawl()` state/resume/error semantics (§3) | Most complex logic, silent-data-loss risk, zero coverage |\n| 2 | `parse_french_date` / `parse_numeric_date` (§1) | Pure functions, cheap to test, has an unhandled `ValueError` gap |\n| 3 | `discover_sitemap_urls` + `_fetch_xml` (§1) | Subtle namespace/gzip/newline handling, easy to regress |\n| 4 | `NewsSource.parse_article` / `_extract_images` (§2) | Largest branch count, needs a scrapling-shaped fake `page` fixture |\n| 5 | `MadagascarTribune`, `FreeNews`, `Moov` custom crawlers (§4) | Only providers with real logic; rest are declarative config |\n| 6 | Provider registry + `main.py` (§5) | Cheap structural tests, catch config typos immediately |\n\nSuggested layout per project convention (`CLAUDE.md`: tests go in `/tests`, not root): `apps/crawler/tests/test_base.py`, `test_providers.py`, `test_main.py`, `test_models.py`, plus a `conftest.py` for the shared `FakeSource`/`make_page` fixtures.\n\nI haven't written any of these files — this is the gap analysis you asked for. Let me know if you'd like me to actually implement the test suite (starting with §3, the highest-value gap).",
